	 <tr><td colspan=1 style='background: silver;font-size: 9.5px;'>139 threads, <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=0>1</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=25>2</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=50>3</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=75>4</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=100>5</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=125>6</a>  page(s) long</td><td style='background: silver;font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=/quest.html?quest=454&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98977100457452></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98977100457452><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98977100457452 style='color: darkblue;'>Spawn rate changed?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 13th 12:23 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was hunting with my cleric in South Karana and checking the Grimrot spawn a couple of times each day. So one night, the 11th May, I finally saw the PH, killed him and started to time the spawn. I brought my lvl 50 enchanter to the spot to kill Grimrot if he'd spawn. Then I went to sleep for 3 hours and logged back on, and the live Grimrot spawned. I summoned a pet and killed him easily. Didn't get any spells to stack on him except tashania though. I went back to sleep, woke up and killed the PH that spawned 3 hours 20 mins later and logged out again. Another PH spawned 3 hours 20 mins after that, killed him too. 3 hours 20 mins later undead Grimrot spawned, wohoo. He went down fast by my DDs. I never checked the EQ time at any occasion, just killed the PHs as soon as they popped. I wonder, is the spawn rate changed, or was I just really lucky to get both spawns within 13.5 hours?<br><br>For the faction part, I turned in 1000 gp and 200 bone chips, that got me from dubios to amiably faction. Turning in 10 koalindl fishes got me to regards you as an ally, and the Aegis of Life was mine =)<br><br>Ayendinel, lvl 22 Cazic Thule worshipping Erudite Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
