<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98924670512544></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98924670512544><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98924670512544 style='color: darkblue;'>Easy way to get faction</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 7th 10:45 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's the easiest way to get faction with the paly's and clerics.<br><br>1. Make a level 1 mele char.<br>2. Jump in the water under the sauser<br>3. Kill the Koatl fish.(all that are there)<br>4. quickly camp and bring your main on<br>5. jump in the water and loot the corpses.<br>6. hand the corpses to Elderic after hailing him he will say something like "out of my way lest I grow wroth and have to hurt you." (the knight that paces around the pool) one at a time.  Each fish is a HUGE faction bump in the right direction and he hands out some pretty nice stuff for lowbies (unfortunately all of it is nodrop).<br><br>I started out at a disadvantage having killed that gnoll in the karana's as a newbie I had unknowingly damaged my faction.  The fish corpses sure did the trick though.  I'm now so warmly that I glow.<br><br>Jaread Warforge<br>Paladin of Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
