<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98552809274667></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98552809274667><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=98552809274667 style='color: darkblue;'>All the info and more!</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 25th 8:48 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hail fellow Norrathians!  I completed this quest a while back.. just been too occupied with other things to post.  Here's a basic rundown of what, where, how needs to be done and the faction to get it.<br><br>1)  As you know Camlend Serbold gives this quest which is in North Qeynos in that flying saucer thingy.  Don't worry about getting the quest now.. just go for grimrot.<br><br>2) Grimrot has 2 versions as you also know.. live and dead.  His PH is always a Standing Putrid Skeleton which stands underneath the tent with NO gold marker in the middle of the circle.  <br><br>I've found the best times to kill the PH to get the Live version is at 5pm to 8pm EQ time.  And the best times to get the Dead version is at 5am to 8am.  Just randomly killing it doesn't work.  Also the PH DOES NOT despawn at 7pm game time.  That has been changed apparently.<br><br>Both versions have a skely pet and they both will use their Harmtouch once attacked.  So have some buffs or a regen up. Live version has pretty good MR while the Undead version doesn't.<br><br>*Now I've heard that people kill the Undead Spawn and get both the heart and the scythe.  This is correct to an extent.  But both versions carry a Pestilence Scythe!  The difference is that the Live Version of Grim drops 2 versions of the Scythe.  One is a NO DROP Pestilence Scythe which has some poison/disease resist and 1 charge of Word of Shadow. (lifetap DOT)  That is the correct scythe!  The other version is just a LORE Pestilence Scythe with no stats. So the Undead drops the heart and LORE scythe and the Live drops the NO DROP scythe and LORE scythe.*<br><br>**Also you can use the charge on the Pest Scythe and it will still work in the final quest.**<br><br>3) Once you have both the NO DROP Scythe and the Heart it's time to work on that faction.  And the best way to check if you faction is good enough is to go to Camlend and ask him about Lord Grimrot.  You can get only so far before he says "I don't think I can trust you with this information yet" Or something to that extent.<br><br>I am a Agnostic High Elf Cleric and conned Amiable when I first started working on the Priests of Life faction.  This is what it took to get the quest (finally) from Camlend.<br><br>1) I turned in 30 Bandit Sash's in South Qeynos.  (info for bandit sash quest is in the South Qeynos quest section)<br>2) I turned in 10 stacks of bone chips to Lashun Novashine (who roams from the Temple of Life to the Newbie area, 2 bonechips at a time per trade slot)<br>3) Also turned in 800gp to Lashun. (2gp at a time)<br><br>By this time I was so Warmly I could have kicked Antonious Bayle in the privates and he would've hugged me for doing it.  ;)<br><br>I then went to Camlend and asked about Grimrot and finally he responded about finding Grim and bringing him his heart and scythe.  I am now the proud owner of an Aegis of Life.<br><br>Hope this helps and sets the records straight.<br><br>Seraphic Invasion<br>Brell Serilis<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
